message.content: A Junonia orithya is a species of butterfly commonly found in Africa, Asia and Australia. It has a wingspan of around 50-60mm and a characteristic pattern of brown, orange and black on its upper wings. The underside of the wings is a duller brown with eye-like markings. The body of the butterfly is thin and lightly covered in fur. The wings are thin but sturdy with a slight curve to their shape. Junonia orithya can be found in a variety of habitats including forests, grasslands and gardens. They are frequently seen in warm, sunny weather and are attracted to flowers for nectar.
